4 A BILL
5 TO BE ENTITLED
6 AN ACT
7
8
9 Relating to Autauga County; to authorize the levy of an
10 additional sales and use tax; and to levy a rental tax.
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
12 Section 1. (a) Beginning September 1, 2026, in addition
13 to any other tax provided by law, there is levied a sales and
14 use tax of one-half of one percent for all business activities
15 covered by Section 45-1-243.01(a)(1), Code of Alabama 1975.
16 (b) The proceeds of this tax shall be deposited in the
17 county general fund.
18 (c) This tax shall be administered according to the
19 procedures established in Part 4 of Article 24 of Chapter 1 of
20 Title 45, Code of Alabama 1975.
21 Section 2. (a) In addition to all other taxes,
22 beginning September 1, 2026, there is levied a three percent
23 privilege tax, to be called a rental tax, on each person
24 leasing or renting tangible personal property in Autauga
25 County.
26 (b) The tax levied pursuant to this section shall
27 parallel the tax imposed by Article 4 of Chapter 12 of Title
28 40, Code of Alabama 1975. This tax shall apply to the same
Page 1

40, Code of Alabama 1975. This tax shall apply to the same
